%% Diagram: Where Node.js work executes — kernel polling vs libuv thread pool
%% Type: flowchart
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
flowchart TB
  JS[JavaScript callsite] --> K{What kind of work?}
  K -->|kernel-async| NB
  K -->|blocking| TP
  K -->|cross-thread| WT
  NB["Non-blocking syscalls\nepoll / kqueue / event ports / IOCP\n• network sockets\n• dns.resolve*"]
  TP["libuv thread pool\ndefault 4, max 1024 (UV_THREADPOOL_SIZE)\n• fs.* (except fs.watch)\n• dns.lookup / dns.lookupService\n• async crypto (pbkdf2, scrypt, randomBytes, ...)\n• async zlib (gzip, deflate, ...)\n• native uv_queue_work"]
  WT["Worker thread\n(separate event loop)\n• Worker.postMessage\n• Atomics.wait / SharedArrayBuffer"]
  NB --> POLL["poll phase wakes;\nrun callback on event-loop thread"]
  TP --> POLL
  WT --> MSG["message arrives via uv_async\non event-loop thread"]
